<figureCitation id="9C982A3EB165FFAC5B779A49FCDFFEBF" box="[820,874,335,361]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1859,1885]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,746,1818]" captionTargetId="figure-98@8.[189,1398,746,1818]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. a–e. Ameroglossum alatum sp. nov. (Almeida &amp; Wanderley 461). a. Reproductive branches. b. Stem. c. Leaf, abaxial side.d. Inflorescence. e. Corolla opened, showing the stamens.f–k. Ameroglossum asperifolium sp. nov. (Felix et al. 15160). f. Reproductive branches.g. Leaf, adaxial side.h. Inflorescence, showing the calyx. i. Flower. j. Flower, showing the stamens. k. Corolla opened, showing the stamens." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4695857" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4695857/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">3f–k</figureCitation>
